        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 4:54PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Greeley, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greeley, Evans, Milliken, Eaton, LaSalle, Kersey, Gilcrest,
Lucerne, Gill, Milton Reservoir, Barnesville, Garden City, Lower
Latham Reservoir, Peckham and Hardin.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
